  "monster": {
    "title": "Weroj.",
    "body": "One of the many lords of Pandemonium, Weroj has an armoured light green body with dragonfly wings and a skull for a head.\n\n<lightgrey>Max HP: 225     </lightgrey><lightgrey> Will: +++      </lightgrey><lightgrey>   AC: ++++     </lightgrey><lightgrey>  EV: +         </lightgrey>                \n<lightgrey>    rF: x..     </lightgrey><lightgrey>   rC: +..      </lightgrey><lightgrey>rPois: +        </lightgrey><lightgrey>rNeg: ∞         </lightgrey><lightgrey>rElec: +        </lightgrey>\n<lightgrey>Threat: High    </lightgrey><lightgrey>Class: Demonic  </lightgrey><lightgrey> Size: Large    </lightgrey><lightgrey> Int: Human     </lightgrey>\nSpeed: 130% (normally travels faster than you)\n\nYou have about 96% to hit with the cursed +9 quick blade \"Enlightened Repose\".\nIt has about 16% to hit you.\n\nAttack  Max Damage    \nHit     24 (base 36)  \n\nIt is immune to torment; and resistant to miasma.\nIt can see invisible.\nIt can fly.\nIt can open doors.\nSPELLSET_PLACEHOLDERTo read a description, press the key listed above. (AdB) indicates damage (the sum of A B-sided dice), (x%) indicates the chance to defeat your Will, and (y) indicates the spell range; shown in red if you are in range.",
    "quote": "",
    "status": "<white>Blind:<lightgrey>\n   This creature cannot see properly. Its accuracy is greatly decreased, it\n   cannot make attacks of opportunity, and spells it casts may sometimes be\n   aimed at the wrong locations.\n   \n   It may also stumble around and eventually lose track of its target,\n   especially if it has low intelligence.\n   \n   <blue>Melee attacks you make against this creature have a chance (proportional to\n   your stealth and weapon skill) of catching it off-guard and dealing increased\n   damage, especially if made with a short blade.<lightgrey>\n\n<white>Dazed:<lightgrey>\n   This creature is temporarily unable to act, but any hostile action will cause\n   it to immediately regain its senses.\n\n<white>Weak:<lightgrey>\n   This creature's melee attacks deal 33% less damage.\n\n<white>Diminished spells:<lightgrey>\n   This creature's spells are less powerful - dealing less damage, being less\n   able to overcome their target's willpower, and occasionally being weaker in\n   other ways.\n\n",
